":0.30,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Adversarial self-check of this GPT-critical lineage\",\"noveltyJustification\":\"Applies the same self-assessment-bias critique to this lineage and downgrades claims that lack direct transcript or executable proof.\",\"sources\":[\"research-prompt.md:95-104\",\".opencode/agents/deep.md:51-59\",\".opencode/node_modules/@opencode-ai/plugin/dist/index.d.ts:225-241\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-01T09:38:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt-critical-1782897047002-qhoaax\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"iteration\":10,\"run\":10,\"newInfoRatio\":0.18,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Synthesis and residual-risk closure\",\"noveltyJustification\":\"No major new source class; consolidates 9 prior iterations into final corrected recommendations and eliminated alternatives.\",\"sources\":[\"research/lineages/sonnet-critical/research.md:13-27\",\"research/lineages/glm-critical/iterations/iteration-001.md:10-29\",\"research/research.md:50-74\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-01T09:41:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt-critical-1782897047002-qhoaax\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"totalIterations\":10,\"answeredCount\":9,\"totalQuestions\":9,\"stopReason\":\"max_iterations\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-01T09:45:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt-critical-1782897047002-qhoaax\",\"generation\":1}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-critical/deep-research-strategy.md\n+# Deep Research Strategy: gpt-critical\n+\n+## Research Topic\n+\n+Critical re-review of GPT behavioral hardening research (packet 031) -- operator-confirmed symptoms, correct for GPT-self-assessment bias, find concrete fixes -- see `research-prompt.md` section 9.\n+\n+## Known Context\n+\n+- Required inputs read before iteration 1: consolidated `research/research.md`, prior `glm-max` and `gpt-fast-high` lineage syntheses, `sonnet-critical` synthesis, and partial `glm-critical` iteration 001.\n+- `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate`.\n+- Operator-confirmed symptoms are treated as ground truth: GPT is slow as `@orchestrate`, invokes the wrong sub-agent, gets stuck on predefined flows, and overthinks/needs literal instructions.\n+\n+## Key Questions\n+\n+1. Where did the prior GPT lineage soften or defer conclusions because it was assessing GPT failures?\n+2. Which concrete mechanism explains stuck predefined flows now that the symptom is confirmed?\n+3. Is ai-council route-proof drift a cosmetic mismatch, a false-fail, or a false-pass?\n+4. What exact orchestrate hardening avoids NDP violations while preserving the deterministic `deep.md` pattern?\n+5. Which plugin hook can enforce route contracts, and what can it not enforce?\n+6. How should the benchmark change after operator-confirmed symptoms?\n+7. Should FIX-5 unpark now, later, or conditionally under a sharper criterion?\n+8. What concrete implementation deliverables should the next phase carry?\n+9. What claims in this GPT-critical lineage need downgrading under the same self-bias audit?\n+\n+## Answered Questions\n+\n+All 9 questions are answered in `research.md` with file-line citations and residual risks.\n+\n+## What Worked\n+\n+- Re-reading source citations instead of relying on prior summaries exposed the Phase 0 Mode-D failure and ai-council false-pass risk.\n+- Treating operator symptoms as confirmed separated mechanism diagnosis from proof-of-existence arguments.\n+- Applying NDP literally prevented an unsafe reading of \"orchestrate dispatches @deep and STOP\".\n+\n+## What Failed\n+\n+- The prior GPT lineage's \"not yet route-proof\" framing was technically accurate but decision-misaligned after operator confirmation.\n+- Prior \"ai-council naming drift\" language under-described the bug; it is a registry/YAML/runtime route-proof contradiction.\n+\n+## Exhausted Approaches\n+\n+- Re-litigating whether GPT symptoms exist.\n+- Treating more smoke evidence as a prerequisite for acknowledging current behavioral failures.\n+- Treating plugin injection as hard custom-agent identity.\n+\n+## Ruled-Out Directions\n+\n+- Immediate ai-council subagent-only conversion.\n+- Literal Task-dispatch from `@orchestrate` to primary `@deep` as a depth-1 worker.\n+- Benchmarking ai-council before route-proof canonicalization.\n+- Using Phase 0 self-assessment gates as a GPT-safe command precondition.\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+\n+Synthesis complete. Recommended next implementation focus: Phase 008 should first replace Phase 0 self-assessment gates and canonicalize ai-council route-proof fields, then apply NDP-safe orchestrate registry reuse, then add plugin/benchmark layers.\n+\n+## Non-Goals\n+\n+- Do not implement code in this lineage.\n+- Do not write outside the lineage artifact directory.\n+- Do not treat route-proof artifacts as the gate for whether operator-confirmed symptoms are real.\n+\n+## Stop Conditions\n+\n+- Stop only after 10 iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n+- Early convergence telemetry is ignored except to broaden angles.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-critical/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+{\n+  \"schemaVersion\": \"deep-research-findings-registry/v1\",\n+  \"lineageLabel\": \"gpt-critical\",\n+  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt-critical-1782897047002-qhoaax\",\n+  \"openQuestions\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"fail-closed-plugin-capability\",\n+      \"question\": \"Can OpenCode `tool.execute.before` reject a Task call directly, or only mutate args?\",\n+      \"status\": \"open\",\n+      \"source\": \"iteration-005\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"mode-d-magnitude\",\n+      \"question\": \"How often does Phase-0/advisory-gate literalism occur across all deep modes and models?\",\n+      \"status\": \"open\",\n+      \"source\": \"iteration-006\"\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"operator-symptoms-real\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Confirmed first-hand by operator; route-proof evidence is no longer required to acknowledge the behavioral problem.\",\n+      \"source\": \"research-prompt.md:91-104\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"phase0-mode-d\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Phase 0 general-agent self-assessment is a concrete Mode-D mechanism and already fired in phase 005 research smoke.\",\n+      \"source\": \"iteration-002\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"council-route-proof\",\n+      \"answer\": \"The ai-council route-proof issue is a false-pass risk against noncanonical identity, not just naming drift.\",\n+      \"source\": \"iteration-003\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"orchestrate-deep-fix\",\n+      \"answer\": \"NDP-safe fix is registry reuse inside orchestrate plus direct leaf dispatch, not a depth-1 Task dispatch to primary @deep.\",\n+      \"source\": \"iteration-004\"\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"keyFindings\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"F1\",\n+      \"title\": \"gpt-fast-high softened confirmed behavioral failures into missing route-proof artifacts\",\n+      \"confidence\": 0.86,\n+      \"iterations\": [1]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"F2\",\n+      \"title\": \"Phase 0 self-assessment gates are a literal-model trap across 8 deep commands\",\n+      \"confidence\": 0.92,\n+      \"iterations\": [2]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"F3\",\n+      \"title\": \"ai-council route-proof currently validates noncanonical council identity\",\n+      \"confidence\": 0.94,\n+      \"iterations\": [3]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"F4\",\n+      \"title\": \"orchestrate should reuse registry resolution, not Task-dispatch a primary @deep worker\",\n+      \"confidence\": 0.82,\n+      \"iterations\": [4, 9]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"F5\",\n+      \"title\": \"plugin guard is feasible as mutation/injection; fail-closed and semantic correctness remain limits\",\n+      \"confidence\": 0.78,\n+      \"iterations\": [5, 9]\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Relitigate whether GPT symptoms exist\",\n+      \"reason\": \"Operator-confirmed symptoms are ground truth for this round.\",\n+      \"iterations\": [1]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Benchmark ai-council before route-proof fix\",\n+      \"reason\": \"Current route-proof path can validate noncanonical values and contaminate benchmark interpretation.\",\n+      \"iterations\": [3, 6]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Treat plugin guard as hard identity\",\n+      \"reason\": \"Available hook surface can inject/mutate prompt or tool args; it does not bind runtime custom-agent identity.\",\n+      \"iterations\": [5]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Immediate FIX-5 solely because symptoms are confirmed\",\n+      \"reason\": \"FIX-5 does not target Phase-0 literalism or generic latency; use conditional unpark after cheap targeted fixes unless post-fix failures persist.\",\n+      \"iterations\": [7]\n+    }\n+  ]\n+}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-critical/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+# Deep Research Dashboard: gpt-critical\n+\n+## Lifecycle\n+\n+- Session: `fanout-gpt-critical-1782897047002-qhoaax`\n+- Status: complete\n+- Stop reason: `max_iterations`\n+- Iterations: 10/10\n+\n+## Iteration Table\n+\n+| run | focus | newInfoRatio | status |\n+|---:|---|---:|---|\n+| 1 | Bias audit of prior GPT synthesis | 0.82 | complete |\n+| 2 | Phase 0 Mode-D firing point | 0.78 | complete |\n+| 3 | ai-council route-proof false-pass | 0.80 | complete |\n+| 4 | NDP-safe orchestrate correction | 0.66 | complete |\n+| 5 | Plugin enforcement mechanism | 0.62 | complete |\n+| 6 | Benchmark redesign | 0.57 | complete |\n+| 7 | FIX-5 unpark criterion | 0.52 | complete |\n+| 8 | Implementation deliverables | 0.48 | complete |\n+| 9 | GPT-critical self-check | 0.30 | complete |\n+| 10 | Final synthesis | 0.18 | complete |\n+\n+## Question Status\n+\n+- Answered: 9/9.\n+- Remaining: fail-closed plugin capability and Mode-D magnitude are carried as implementation/benchmark residuals, not blockers for synthesis.\n+\n+## Trend\n+\n+- newInfoRatio trend: `0.82 -> 0.78 -> 0.80 -> 0.66 -> 0.62 -> 0.57 -> 0.52 -> 0.48 -> 0.30 -> 0.18`.\n+- Convergence before iteration 10 treated as telemetry only per charter.\n+\n+## Dead Ends\n+\n+- Re-litigating operator-confirmed symptoms.\n+- Treating ai-council route proof as cosmetic naming drift.\n+- Treating plugin injection as hard custom-agent identity.\n+- Using external smoke as the only possible justification for action.\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+\n+Phase 008 planning/implementation should prioritize deterministic command invocation context and route-proof canonicalization before measurement and plugin layers.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-critical/resource-map.md\n+# Resource Map: gpt-critical Evidence\n+\n+## Prior Syntheses\n+\n+- `research/research.md` -- consolidated prior 30-iteration lineages.\n+- `research/lineages/glm-max/research.md` -- non-GPT prior lineage with Mode-D hypothesis.\n+- `research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/research.md` -- GPT prior lineage under bias review.\n+- `research/lineages/sonnet-critical/research.md` -- completed critical lineage.\n+- `research/lineages/glm-critical/iterations/iteration-001.md` -- partial critical lineage.\n+\n+## Primary Code Evidence\n+\n+- `.opencode/commands/deep/*.md` -- Phase 0 general-agent self-check pattern.\n+- `.opencode/agents/deep.md` -- deterministic registry router pattern.\n+- `.opencode/agents/orchestrate.md` -- broad primary orchestrator, NDP, dispatch template.\n+- `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_auto.yaml` -- council emitted route fields and validator expectations.\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-topic.cjs` -- council runtime route-proof writer.\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts` -- strict route-proof comparator.\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json` -- canonical workflowMode/runtime/agent mapping.\n+- `.opencode/node_modules/@opencode-ai/plugin/dist/index.d.ts` -- installed plugin hook surface.\n+\n+## Packet Evidence\n+\n+- `005-gpt-verification-smoke/verification-smoke.md` -- Phase 005 failed/blocked smoke table.\n+- `005-gpt-verification-smoke/implementation-summary.md` -- verification summary and limitations.\n+- `006-host-hard-identity-fix5/decision-record.md` -- existing FIX-5 trigger.\n+- `001-deep-agent-router-and-orchestration/research/research.md` -- original root-cause and hard-identity ceiling.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-critical/deep-research-config.json\nA .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-critical/deep-research-state.jsonl\nA .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-critical/deep-research-strategy.md\nA .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-critical/deep-research-findings-registry.json\nA .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-critical/deep-research-dashboard.md\nA .opencode/specs/deep-loops/031-deep-loop-issues-with-gpt-opencode/007-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/gpt-critical/resource-map.md","metadata"